credit.credit-words: 4. But water by itself is dead, As we were without Christ. So those who come without the Head Will pay an awful price.
3. The Father calls the nations home; He sent His preachers out To summon those who loved to roam Through twisted sins and doubts.
5. The Spirit washes sin away, The Spirit gives us faith. We come into the Father’s day, The first day and the eighth.
